# Synthetic Finance Data 3M

An open-source synthetic dataset created to help train and benchmark AI systems on finance-oriented tasks at meaningful scale.

## Why this dataset exists

Financial AI development is often bottlenecked by limited access to clean, reusable, and shareable data. This project offers a practical alternative: high-volume synthetic data designed for experimentation and model development.

## Highlights

- ~3M synthetic finance records for large-scale training loops
- Built for supervised fine-tuning, evaluation, and pipeline testing
- Useful for prototyping finance-specific language and prediction tasks
- Published openly on Hugging Face for reproducible research

## Use cases

- Domain adaptation for financial language models
- Stress-testing data pipelines and feature extractors
- Benchmarking model quality before production data integration
